parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Drive Train Noise and Vibration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise and vibration from the front drive train can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Dragging sound from the front drive train
vibrations on the highway
noise that comes and subsides.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft assembly can cause sudden deceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: Sudden increase in engine RPMs
vehicle deceleration
acceleration without warning when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, loss of control, and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
engine racing
wheels spinning freely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Bump or Jerk after Coming to a Stop
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden bump or jerk can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Bump or jerk after coming to a stop
only occurs when the A/C is running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shifting issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: Intermittent shifting
vehicle acting like transmission is in neutral
engine revving up before transmission engages
tire slippage
loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration Due to Throttle Body or Pedal Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without warning
and may continue to accelerate even after the driver removes their foot from the accelerator pedal. In some cases
the vehicle may lunge forward or continue moving even after shifting into neutral gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Floor Mat Interference with Accelerator Pedal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Floor mat interference with the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The floor mat slides forward and jams the accelerator pedal
causing the vehicle to continue accelerating even after the driver removes their foot from the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Issues Leading to Unintended Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
often while making turns or driving at high speeds
and may require shifting into neutral gear and applying the brakes to stop the vehicle. In some cases
the transmission may make unusual noises or the vehicle may lunge forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Malfunction due to Faulty Spiral Cable
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty spiral cable can cause the airbag warning light to remain off or malfunction, leading to a potential failure of the airbag system in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains off or does not illuminate
the airbag system is non-functional
the system fails to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to respond to Takata recall notices can lead to prolonged exposure to potentially faulty airbag systems, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: No response or inadequate response from dealerships to recall notices
lack of communication regarding recall repairs
failure to perform necessary repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Malfunction due to Interference from Other Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system due to interference from other components, such as the fire extinguisher, can cause the airbag system to become non-functional, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains off or does not illuminate
the airbag system is non-functional
the system fails to deploy in the event of a crash.
